  "body": "CoreDNS 1.1.1 ...\r\nI found that the `continue` option causes a response re-write rule to not work.\r\n\r\nFor example...\r\n```\r\n      rewrite continue {\r\n        name regex test\\.local kubernetes.default.svc.cluster.local\r\n        answer name kubernetes\\.default\\.svc\\.cluster\\.local test.local\r\n      }\r\n```\r\n... fails to rewrite the response ...\r\n```\r\ndnstools# dig test.local. -t A\r\n;; Question section mismatch: got kubernetes.default.svc.cluster.local/A/IN\r\n```\r\n... while ...\r\n```\r\n      rewrite stop {\r\n        name regex test\\.local kubernetes.default.svc.cluster.local\r\n        answer name kubernetes\\.default\\.svc\\.cluster\\.local test.local\r\n      }\r\n```\r\n... works fine ...\r\n```\r\ndnstools# dig test.local. -t A\r\n\r\n; <<>> DiG 9.11.1-P1 <<>> test.local. -t A\r\n;; global options: +cmd\r\n;; Got answer:\r\n;; ->>HEADER<<- opcode: QUERY, status: NOERROR, id: 39949\r\n;; flags: qr aa rd ra; QUERY: 1, ANSWER: 1, AUTHORITY: 0, ADDITIONAL: 1\r\n\r\n;; OPT PSEUDOSECTION:\r\n; EDNS: version: 0, flags:; udp: 4096\r\n; COOKIE: bf7f5bede8bb8ece (echoed)\r\n;; QUESTION SECTION:\r\n;test.local.\t\t\tIN\tA\r\n\r\n;; ANSWER SECTION:\r\ntest.local.\t\t5\tIN\tA\t10.0.0.1\r\n\r\n;; Query time: 0 msec\r\n;; SERVER: 10.0.0.10#53(10.0.0.10)\r\n;; WHEN: Fri Apr 20 18:54:20 UTC 2018\r\n;; MSG SIZE  rcvd: 67\r\n```",
